          <h1 style=" font-size: 60px; text-align: center; color: white;"><i>ADENIUM</i></h1>
    

    
            <p style="color: white;font-size: 30px; text-align: left;"><i>Adenium is a genus of flowering plants in the family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1819. It is native to Africa and the Arabian Peninsula.</i></p>
        
        
    <div class="Weather">
        <h2 style=" font-size: 30px; text-align: left; color: white;"><strong><i>Weather Conditions:</i></strong></h2>
            <p style="color: white;font-size: 20px;">Because they can tolerate dry conditions, adeniums are well suited for the home environment being able to tolerate quite a bit of neglect. Keep temperatures high, preferably above 60˙F, although they can take it a bit cooler if grown very dry. Really the hotter, the better, so a 70˙F or higher air temperature is best.</p>      
    </div>

    <div class="Soil">    
        <h3 style=" font-size: 30px; text-align: left; color: white;"><strong><i>Soil requirement:</i></strong></h3>        
            <p style="color: white;font-size: 20px;">Soil is very important. Adenium plants should have a mixture of cactus soil with gritty sand or lava rocks for good drainage.</p>
    </div>        

    <div class="Place">     
        <h3 style=" font-size: 30px; text-align: left; color: white;"><strong><i>Place of cultivation:</i></strong></h3>
            <p style="color: white;font-size: 20px;">Adeniums is a very rare ornamental plant and this farm is one of the largest and oldest farm dedicated for various kinds of adenium varieties . The 15 acre farm is located in a quiet tamil village , about 1.5 hours from chennai airport and in a very scenic location on border of Tamilnadu and Andra pradesh .</p>
